{"title_page": "Fanny Bertrand", "text_new": "{{short description|French para table tennis player}}\n{{Infobox athlete\n| name = Fanny Bertrand\n| nickname = \n| image = \n| imagesize = \n| caption = \n| nationality = \n| sport = [[Para table tennis]]\n| disability = [[Paraplegia]]\n| disability_class = [[Para table tennis#Classification|C3]]\n| event = \n| club = \n| coach = Guillaume Jean\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1976|12|28|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Orange, Vaucluse]], [[France]]\n| residence = [[N\u00eemes]], France\n| retired= \n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| height = \n| weight = \n| pb = \n| country = {{FRA}} \n| medaltemplates =\n{{Medal|Sport|[[Para table tennis]]}}\n{{Medal|Country|{{FRA}}}}\n{{Medal|Competition|[[Paralympic Games]]}}\n{{Medal|Bronze|[[2008 Summer Paralympics|2008 Beijing]]|[[Table tennis at the 2008 Summer Paralympics - Women's team - Class 1-3|Women's team C1-3]]}}\n{{Medal|Competition|[[European Para Table Tennis Championships|European Championships]]}}\n{{Medal|Gold|2007 Kranjska Gora|Women's team C2-3}}\n{{Medal|Gold|2009 Genoa|Women's team C3}}\n{{Medal|Silver|2011 Split|Women's teams C3}}\n{{Medal|Silver|2013 Lignano|Women's singles C3}}\n{{Medal|Bronze|2007 Kranjska Gora|Women's singles C3}}\n{{Medal|Bronze|2013 Lignano|Women's teams C1-3}}\n}}\n\n'''Fanny Bertrand''' (born December 28, 1976) is a [[French people|French]] [[para table tennis]] player. She took up table tennis in 2002 as part of her rehabilitation after sustaining a spinal injury in a road accident in 2000. She has won team titles with [[Marie-Christine Fillou]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://france-paralympique.fr/paralympiens/fanny-bertrand/|title=Fanny Bertrand - Profile (in French)|last=|first=|date=12 February 2020|website=France Paralympique|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://stats.ipttc.org/en/profiles/2442|title=Fanny Bertrand - IPTTF Profile|last=|first=|date=12 February 2020|website=International Para Table Tennis Federation|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nHer grandfather Robert Bertrand founded the eponymous [[basketball]] club [[FRJ Saint Blaise]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.e-tribune.fr/index.php/2014-10-22-08-45-07/7932-tennis-de-table-pour-la-bollenoise-fanny-bertrand-un-5e-titre-de-championne-de-france|title=Tennis de table: Pour la Bollenoise Fanny Bertrand, un 5e titre de championne de France (in French)|last=|first=|date=9 July 2016|website=La Tribune|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IPC athlete|fanny-bertrand}}\n* {{CPSF|fanny-bertrand}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bertrand, Fanny}}\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Orange, Vaucluse]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from N\u00eemes]]\n[[Category:Paralympic table tennis players of France]]\n[[Category:Table tennis players at the 2008 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Table tennis players at the 2012 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2008 Summer Paralympics]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|French para table tennis player}}\n{{Infobox athlete\n| name = Fanny Bertrand\n| nickname = \n| image = \n| imagesize = \n| caption = \n| nationality = \n| sport = [[Para table tennis]]\n|disability = [[Paraplegia]]\n|disability_class = [[Para table tennis#Classification|C3]]\n| event = \n| club = \n| coach = Guillaume Jean\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1976|12|28|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Orange, Vaucluse]], [[France]]\n| residence = [[N\u00eemes]], France\n| retired= \n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| height = \n| weight = \n| pb = \n| country = {{FRA}} \n| medaltemplates =\n{{Medal|Sport|[[Para table tennis]]}}\n{{Medal|Country|{{FRA}}}}\n{{Medal|Competition|[[Paralympic Games]]}}\n{{Medal|Bronze|[[2008 Summer Paralympics|2008 Beijing]]|[[Table tennis at the 2008 Summer Paralympics - Women's team - Class 1-3|Women's team C1-3]]}}\n{{Medal|Competition|[[European Para Table Tennis Championships|European Championships]]}}\n{{Medal|Gold|2007 Kranjska Gora|Women's team C2-3}}\n{{Medal|Gold|2009 Genoa|Women's team C3}}\n{{Medal|Silver|2011 Split|Women's teams C3}}\n{{Medal|Silver|2013 Lignano|Women's singles C3}}\n{{Medal|Bronze|2007 Kranjska Gora|Women's singles C3}}\n{{Medal|Bronze|2013 Lignano|Women's teams C1-3}}\n}}\n\n'''Fanny Bertrand''' (born December 28, 1976) is a [[French people|French]] [[para table tennis]] player. She took up table tennis in 2002 as part of her rehabilitation after sustaining a spinal injury in a road accident in 2000. She has won team titles with [[Marie-Christine Fillou]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://france-paralympique.fr/paralympiens/fanny-bertrand/|title=Fanny Bertrand - Profile (in French)|last=|first=|date=12 February 2020|website=France Paralympique|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://stats.ipttc.org/en/profiles/2442|title=Fanny Bertrand - IPTTF Profile|last=|first=|date=12 February 2020|website=International Para Table Tennis Federation|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nHer grandfather Robert Bertrand founded the eponymous [[basketball]] club [[FRJ Saint Blaise]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.e-tribune.fr/index.php/2014-10-22-08-45-07/7932-tennis-de-table-pour-la-bollenoise-fanny-bertrand-un-5e-titre-de-championne-de-france|title=Tennis de table: Pour la Bollenoise Fanny Bertrand, un 5e titre de championne de France (in French)|last=|first=|date=9 July 2016|website=La Tribune|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Orange, Vaucluse]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from N\u00eemes]]\n[[Category:Paralympic table tennis players of France]]\n[[Category:Table tennis players at the 2008 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Table tennis players at the 2012 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2008 Summer Paralympics]]\n", "name_user": "Zyxw", "label": "safe", "comment": "add links and DEFAULTSORT", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fanny_Bertrand"}
{"title_page": "Ross County F.C. Records and Statistics", "text_new": "[[Ross County F.C.|Ross County Football Club]] are a Scottish professional [[association football]] club based in [[Dingwall]]. Ross County joined the [[Highland Football League]] in 1929, and then were one of two clubs voted into the [[Scottish Professional Football League]] System in 1994.\n\nThe club's record appearance maker is [[Michael Gardyne]], who has made Over 400 appearances through four spells at the club. Gardyne is also the club's record goalscorer, scoring over 70 goals in major competitions during his time at Ross County.\n\nThis list encompasses the major honours won by Ross County, records set by the club, their managers and their players.  The player records section includes details of the club's leading goalscorers and those who have made most appearances in first-team competitions. It also records notable achievements by Ross County players on the international stage, and the highest transfer fees paid and received by the club. Attendance records are also included in the list.\n\n==Honours==\n===League===\n* '''[[Scottish Football League First Division|First Division]]/[[Scottish Championship|Championship]] (second tier)'''\n** '''Winners''' (2): [[2011\u201312 Scottish First Division|2011\u201312]], [[2018\u201319 Scottish Championship|2018\u201319]]\n* '''[[Scottish Football League Second Division|Second Division]] (third tier)'''\n** '''Winners''' (1): [[2007\u201308 Scottish Second Division|2007\u201308]]\n* '''[[Scottish Football League Third Division|Third Division]] (fourth tier)'''\n** '''Winners''' (1): [[1998\u201399 in Scottish football|1998\u201399]]\n* '''[[Highland Football League]]'''\n** '''Winners''' (3): 1966\u201367, [[1990\u201391 Highland Football League|1990\u201391]], [[1991\u201392 Highland Football League|1991\u201392]]\n** ''Runners-up (2)'': 1967\u201368, 1972\u201373\n* '''[[North Caledonian Football League]]'''\n** '''Winners''' (2): 1965\u201366, 1996\u201397\n\n===Cup===\n* '''[[Scottish Cup]]'''\n** ''Runners-up (1)'': [[2010 Scottish Cup Final|2009\u201310]]\n* '''[[Scottish League Cup]]:'''\n** '''Winners''' (1): [[2015\u201316 Scottish League Cup|2015\u201316]]\n* '''[[Scottish Challenge Cup|Challenge Cup]]'''\n** '''Winners''' (3): [[2006\u201307 Scottish Challenge Cup|2006\u201307]], [[2010\u201311 Scottish Challenge Cup|2010\u201311]], [[2018\u201319 Scottish Challenge Cup|2018\u201319]]\n** ''Runners-up (2)'': [[2004 Scottish Challenge Cup Final|2004\u201305]], [[2008 Scottish Challenge Cup Final|2008\u201309]]\n* '''[[Scottish Qualifying Cup|Qualifying Cup (North)]]'''\n** '''Winners''' (1): [[1993\u201394 Scottish Cup|1993\u201394]]\n** ''Runners-up (5)'': [[1933\u201334 Scottish Cup|1933\u201334]], [[1965\u201366 Scottish Cup|1965\u201366]], [[1969\u201370 Scottish Cup|1969\u201370]], [[1972\u201373 Scottish Cup|1972\u201373]], [[1973\u201374 Scottish Cup|1973\u201374]]\n* '''[[North of Scotland Cup]]'''\n** '''Winners''' (6): 1929\u201330, 1969\u201370, 1971\u201372, 1991\u201392, 2006\u201307, 2018\u201319\n* '''[[Highland League Cup]]'''\n**'''Winners''' (4): 1949\u201350, 1968\u201369, 1978\u201379, 1991\u201392\n\n===Youth===\n* '''[[SPFL Development League]] (Under-20)'''\n** '''Winners''' (1): [[2016\u201317 SPFL Development League|2016\u201317]]\n\n==Player records==\n===Individual Records===\n* '''Most Appearance Holder''': [[Michael Gardyne]] (409)\n* '''Record Goalscorer''': [[Michael Gardyne]] (71)\n* '''Most Goals in a season (all competitions)''': [[Andrew Barrowman]] (29)\n* '''Most Goals in a season (league)''': [[Andrew Barrowman]] (24)\n*'''Most Clean Sheets''': [[Nicky Walker]] (54)\n*'''Most Hat-Tricks''': [[Liam Boyce]] (5)\n\n===Most appearances===\n''As of 24 February 2020 (competitive matches only):''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! #\n! Name\n! Career\n! Apps\n! Goals\n|-\n| 1\n| {{Flagicon|SCO}} '''[[Michael Gardyne]]'''\n| 2006\u20132007, 2008\u20132012, 2014\u2013201