he Power of Culture|year=2002|last1=Blanning|first1=T. C. W.|isbn=9780198227458}}\n* Cameron, Euan. ''Early Modern Europe: An Oxford History'' (2001)\n* Friedrich, Carl J. ''The Age of the Baroque, 1610-1660'' (1962); Despite the title, this is a wide-ranging Social, cultural, political and diplomatic history of Europe; [https://archive.org/details/ageofbaroque100frie 14-day borrowing copy]\n* Hesmyr, Atle. ''Scandinavia in the Early Modern Era; From Peasant Revolts and Witch Hunts to Constitution Drafting Yeomen'' (2014)\n* {{cite book|doi=10.4324/9781315837093|title=The Rise of the Great Powers 1648 - 1815|year=2014|last1=McKay|first1=Derek|isbn=9781315837093}}\n* Rice, Eugene F. ''The Foundations of Early Modern Europe, 1460-1559'' (2nd ed. 1994) 240 pp\n* Merriman, John. ''A History of Modern Europe: From the Renaissance to the Present'' (3rd ed. 2009, 2 vol), 1412 pp\n* [[Hamish Scott (historian)|Scott, Hamish]], ed. ''The Oxford Handbook of Early Modern European History, 1350-1750: Volume I: Peoples and Place'' (2015).\n** {{cite journal|doi=10.1093/oxfordhb/9780199597260.001.0001|title=The Oxford Handbook of Early Modern European History, 1350-1750|year=2015|isbn=9780199597260}}\n* Stoye, John. ''Europe Unfolding, 1648-1688'' (2nd ed. 2000).\n* {{cite book|doi=10.4324/9780203425985|title=The Making of Modern Europe, 1648-1780|year=2003|last1=Treasure|first1=Geoffrey|isbn=9780203425985}}\n* Wiesner, Merry E. ''Early Modern Europe, 1450-1789'' (Cambridge History of Europe) (2006)\n \n===Past perspectives on modern European history===\n* Earle, Edward Mead. [https://archive.org/details/outlineofmodernh00earl ''An Outline of Modern History; A Syllabus with Map Studies'']. New York: Macmillan Co, 1921.\n* Taylor, William Cooke, Charles Duke Yonge, and G.W. Cox. [https://books.google.com/books?id=bjQYAAAAYAAJ ''The Student's Manual of Modern History; Containing the Rise and Progress of the Principal European Nations, Their Political History, and the Changes in Their Social Condition; with a History of the Colonies Founded by Europeans'']. 1880.\n \n===19th century===\n* Anderson, M.S. ''The Ascendancy of Europe: 1815-1914'' (3rd ed. 2003)\n* Blanning, T.C.W. ed. ''The Nineteenth Century: Europe 1789-1914'' (Short Oxford History of Europe) (2000) 320 pp\n* Brinton, Crane. ''A Decade of Revolution, 1789-1799'' (1934).\" [https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.74354 online] in Langer series on history of Europe.\n* Bruun, Geoffrey. ''Europe and the French Imperium, 1799-1814'' (1938) [https://archive.org/download/in.ernet.dli.2015.183653/2015.183653.Europe-And-The-French-Imperium-1799-1814_text.pdf online].\n* Cameron, Rondo. ''France and the Economic Development of Europe, 1800-1914: Conquests of Peace and Seeds of War'' (1961), wide-ranging economic and business history.\n* Evans, Richard J. ''The Pursuit of Power: Europe 1815-1914'' (2016), 934 pp\n* Gildea, Robert. ''Barricades and Borders: Europe 1800-1914'' (Short Oxford History of the Modern World) (3rd ed. 2003) 544 pp, [https://www.questia.com/read/55547824/barricades-and-borders-europe-1800-1914 online 2nd ed, 1996]\n* {{cite book|doi=10.1007/978-1-4039-3757-5|title=Napoleon and the Transformation of Europe|year=2003|last1=Grab|first1=Alexander|isbn=978-0-333-68275-3}}\n* Kertesz, G.A. ed ''Documents in the Political History of the European Continent 1815-1939'' (1968), 507 pp; several hundred short documents\n* Mason, David S. ''A Concise History of Modern Europe: Liberty, Equality, Solidarity'' (2011), since 1700\n* Merriman, John, and J.M. Winter, eds. ''Europe 1789 to 1914: Encyclopedia of the Age of Industry and Empire'' (5 vol. 2006)\n* Ramm, Agatha. ''Europe in the Nineteenth Century 1789-1905'' (1984).\n* Richardson, Hubert N.B. ''A Dictionary of Napoleon and His Times'' (1921) [https://archive.org/details/dictionaryofnapo00rich online free] 489 pp\n* Steinberg, Jonathan. ''Bismarck: A Life'' (2011)\n* Salmi, Hannu. ''19th Century Europe: A Cultural History'' (2008).\n* Taylor, A.J.P. ''[[The Struggle for Mastery in Europe 1848-1918]]'' (1954) [https://archive.org/details/struggleformaste00ajpt online free]; Advanced diplomatic history\n* Thomson, David. ''Europe Since Napoleon'' (1923) [https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.98593 online free] 524 pp\n\n===Since 1900===\n* Brose, Eric Dorn. ''A History of Europe in the Twentieth Century'' (2004) 548 pp\n* Buchanan, Tom. ''Europe's Troubled Peace: 1945 to the Present'' (Blackwell History of Europe) (2012)\n* Cook, Bernard A. ''Europe Since 1945: An Encyclopedia'' (2 vol; 2001), 1465 pp\n* Davies, Norman. ''[[Europe at War 1939-1945: No Simple Victory]]'' (2008)\n* Dear, I.C.B. and M.R.D. Foot, eds. ''The Oxford Companion to World War II'' (2006)\n* Frank, Matthew. ''Making Minorities History: Population Transfer in Twentieth-Century Europe'' (Oxford UP, 2017). 464 pp. [http://www.h-net.msu.edu/reviews/showrev.php?id=52226 online review]\n* Grenville, J.A.S. ''A History of the World in the Twentieth Century'' (1994). [https://archive.org/details/historyofworldin00gren online free]\n* Hallock, Stephanie A. ''The World in the 20th Century: A Thematic Approach'' (2012)\n* {{cite book|doi=10.1515/9781400865598|title=Out of Ashes|year=2015|last1=Jarausch|first1=Konrad H.|isbn=9781400865598}}\n* Judt, Tony. ''Postwar: A History of Europe Since 1945'' (2006)\n* Martel, Gordon, ed. ''A Companion to Europe, 1900-1950'' (2011) 32 essays by scholars; emphasis on historiography\n* Mazower, Mark. ''Dark Continent: Europe's Twentieth Century'' (2000) 512 pp\n* Merriman, John, and Jay Winter, eds. ''Europe Since 1914: Encyclopedia of the Age War and Reconstruction'' (5 vol. 2006)\n* {{cite book|doi=10.1017/CBO9780511820465|title=Civil War in Europe, 1905\u20131949|year=2011|last1=Payne|first1=Stanley G.|isbn=9780511820465}}\n* Paxton, Robert O., and Julie Hessler. ''Europe in the twentieth century'' ([https://www.amazon.com/Europe-Twentieth-Century-Robert-Paxton-ebook/dp/B00B7L8ZQ2/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1482129779&sr=8-1&keywords=Paxton%2C+Robert+O.%2C+and+Julie+Hessler.+Europe+in+the+twentieth+century.+Cengage+Learning%2C+2011. 5th edition 2011].\n* Pollard, Sidney, ed. ''Wealth and Poverty: an Economic History of the 20th Century'' (1990), 260 pp; global perspective [https://archive.org/details/wealthpovertyeco00poll online free]\n* [[Raymond James Sontag|Sontag, Raymond James.]] ''A broken world, 1919-1939'' (1972), wide ranging history of interwar Europe; [https://archive.org/details/brokenworld1919100sont/page/n11 online free to borrow]\n* Stearns, Peter, ed. ''The Encyclopedia of World History'' (2001)\n* Stone, Dan, ed. ''The Oxford Handbook of Postwar European History'' (2015).\n* Ther, Philipp. ''Europe since 1989: A History'' (Princeton UP, 2016) [http://press.princeton.edu/titles/10812.html excerpt], 440 pp\n* Toynbee, Arnold, ed. ''Survey Of International Affairs: Hitler's Europe 1939-1946'' (1954) [https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.84095 online]\n* {{cite book|doi=10.1017/CBO9780511818639|title=A World at Arms|year=2005|last1=Weinberg|first1=Gerhard L.|isbn=9780511818639}}\n\n===Agriculture and economy===\n* {{cite book|doi=10.1007/978-1-4020-9840-6|title=The Western European Loess Belt|year=2009|last1=Bakels|first1=Corrie C.|isbn=978-1-4020-9839-0}}\n* [[Iv\u00e1n T. Berend|Berend, Iv\u00e1n T.]] ''An Economic History of Twentieth-Century Europe'' (2013)\n* {{cite book|doi=10.1017/CBO9780511844867|title=Europe|year=2010|last1=Berend|first1=Ivan T.|isbn=9780511844867|url=https://semanticscholar.org/paper/c1603a42ec2e35de43885ee71734ee32f20a24be}}\n* {{cite book|doi=10.1017/CBO9780511794841|title=The Cambridge Economic History of Modern Europe|year=2010|isbn=9780511794841}}\n* {{cite book|doi=10.1007/978-94-017-6137-6|title=Land and Labor in Europe in the Twentieth Century|year=1965|last1=Dovring|first1=Folke|last2=Dovring|first2=Karin|isbn=978-94-017-5756-0}}\n* Gras, Norman. ''A history of agriculture in Europe and America'' (1925). [https://archive.today/20121205041741/http://chla.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/text-idx?c=chla;idno=2845579 free online edition]\n* Milward, Alan S. and S.B. Saul. ''The Development of the Economies of Continental Europe: 1850-1914'' (1977)\n* Murray, Jacqueline. ''The First European Agriculture'' (1970)\n* Pollard, Sidney, ed. ''Wealth and Poverty: an Economic History of the 20th Century'' (1990), 260 pp; global perspective [https://archive.org/details/wealthpovertyeco00poll online free]\n* Pounds, N.J.G. ''An Economic History of Medieval Europe'' (1994)\n* [[Bernard Slicher van Bath|Slicher van Bath, B.H.]] ''The agrarian history of Western Europe, AD 500-1850'' (1966)\n* Thorp, William Long. ''Business Annals: United States, England, France, Germany, Austria, Russia, Sweden, Netherlands, Italy, Argentina, Brazil, Canada, South Africa, Australia, India, Japan, China'' (1926) capsule summary of conditions in each country for each quarter-year 1790-1925\n \n\n===Diplomacy===\n* Albrecht-Carri\u00e9, Ren\u00e9. ''A Diplomatic History of Europe Since the Congress of Vienna'' (1958), 736 pp, basic introduction 1815-1955\n* Black, Jeremy. ''A History of Diplomacy'' (2011)\n* {{cite book|doi=10.1007/978-1-137-09934-1|title=European International Relations 1648\u20131815|year=2002|last1=Black|first1=Jeremy|isbn=978-0-333-96451-4}}\n* Kertesz, G.A. ed ''Documents in the Political History of the European Continent 1815-1939'' (1968), 507 pp; several hundred short documents\n* Langer, William. ''An Encyclopedia of World History'' (5th ed. 1973), very detailed outline\n* Macmillan, Margaret. ''The War That Ended Peace: The Road to 1914'' (2013) cover 1890s to 1914\n* Mowat, R.B. ''History of European Diplomacy, 1451-1789'' (1928) 324 pages [https://www.questia.com/library/23721/a-history-of-european-diplomacy-1451-1789 online]\n* Petrie, Charles. ''Earlier diplomatic history, 1492-1713'' (1949), covers all of Europe; [https://web.archive.or